  footnotes: []
english:
  title: On This Moment
  author: Seo Geo-jeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Ten years have worn my face to thinness,
    A month has passed without combing my hair.
    Old ailments pile upon new ones—
    My idle dwelling seems a hermit's retreat.

    Beside the brazier I warm medicinal wine,
    Dipping my brush to write prescriptions.
    I trusted in my own clumsy management,
    Yet now I see how distant old friends have grown.
  footnotes:
    - The poem reflects on the physical and social toll of prolonged illness and seclusion, common themes in Korean literati poetry of the Joseon period.
    - The contrast between self-reliant solitude and the erosion of friendships suggests the speaker's gradual withdrawal from society despite initial confidence in his autonomy.
